  <Contents>
    <Content contentid="3694" contenttypeid="INTRO" desc="Introduction">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Haleana is a bright, sleek, modern villa – a place to holiday with friends and family, celebrate a wedding or unwind in tranquillity.&nbsp; With spectacular views over the pristine, near-deserted Nai Thon Beach on Phuket’s northwest coast, this six-bedroomed villa wraps you in its luxurious embrace while a team of full-time staff indulge you with impeccable service.&nbsp; Days at Villa Haleana unfold with dips in the private pool, delicious meals prepared by your personal Thai chef and hours spent relaxing and socialising in the plush living areas.&nbsp; Restore your senses in the villa’s private spa room after enjoying a workout in the gym, or just sit back and watch the vivid tropical sunsets.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3699" contenttypeid="ABTV" desc="About Villa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>This six-bedroomed holiday haven flaunts magical sea and sunset views from its hillside setting above beautiful Nai Thon Beach.&nbsp; With its modern tropical style, large comfortable living areas and attentive staff, Villa Haleana is ideal for families or groups seeking to unwind in tranquillity or celebrate a wedding or other special occasion.&nbsp; Found along the lesser-travelled northwest Phuket coast, the villa is well situated to explore the area’s endless powder-soft beaches and rural landscapes.</p><p>Effortlessly elegant yet warmly welcoming, two-storey Villa Haleana is crowned by peak-roofed pavilions inspired by traditional Thai designs, while its bright, modern interior spaces are swathed in gorgeous marble and polished woods.&nbsp; Complete relaxation and rejuvenation is guaranteed courtesy of the villa’s private 18-metre pool, lavish spa room and gym, as well as multiple areas to rest, dine and entertain.&nbsp; The two master bedrooms make private retreats fit for royalty, and every bedroom offers stunning sea views.&nbsp; Throughout your stay you’ll enjoy the warm hospitality of a team of full-time staff including a talented Thai chef and friendly English-speaking villa manager, who will ensure your every need is met.</p><p>Nai Thon – just a short walk from the villa – is quite simply one of Phuket’s most exquisite beaches: a one-kilometre stretch of pristine, powder-soft sand surrounded by lush parkland.&nbsp; Spend the day relaxing on the beach, or explore the turquoise waters by snorkel or stand-up paddle, and then head out to one of the island’s world-class restaurants or beachfront bars or cafés for the evening.&nbsp; All are within easy reach of Villa Haleana, as are several of Phuket’s most interesting sights and leisure activities, including golf and yacht charters.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3705" contenttypeid="STAFF" desc="Staff">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Guests at Malaiwana enjoy the exclusive care of a full-time manager, chef and housekeeping staff with flexible working hours.&nbsp;  With this team’s blend of warm Thai hospitality and professional standards of service, a restful and well-pampered holiday is assured.&nbsp; Please feel free to discuss your group’s preferences with the manager.&nbsp;  For example, just let the manager know whether you’d prefer staff to be visibly ‘front of house’, ready to attend to your every whim throughout the day, or if you’d prefer more privacy, with staff staying discreetly out of sight until you need them.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Manager]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>The English-speaking manager liaises with guests, and communicates their preferences to the chef and staff to ensure that everything is handled with smooth efficiency.&nbsp; An excellent source of local knowledge, the manager will be pleased to provide suggestions for sightseeing and dining out in Phuket, as well as assistance with tour and transport bookings.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Chef]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>The skilled chef prepares breakfast, lunch, dinner and snacks according to guest requirements.&nbsp; Meals are prepared from a suggestion menu of mainly Thai and some Western dishes, tailored to accommodate special dietary needs and guest preferences.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Housekeeping]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>A team of staff handles daily housekeeping duties, as well as assisting the chef with kitchen and dining service. </p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Pool  ]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Regular pool-cleaning and maintenance services are taken care of by a team of estate staff.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Security ]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Estate staff keep Malaiwana safe and secure 24 hours a day.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3709" contenttypeid="LYT" desc="Layout">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Villa Haleana is arranged over two storeys in a pair of pavilions positioned for prime sea and sunset views.&nbsp; Enter the villa on the upper floor, via a lovely landscaped garden.&nbsp; An open-plan living and dining area plus the guests’ and chef’s kitchens are housed in the larger pavilion.&nbsp; In the smaller pavilion, a media room leads to the first master suite.&nbsp; Extending across the front of the villa is the 18-metre pool and surrounding deck with awe-inspiring views.&nbsp; Take the lift or stairs down to the second master suite, four guest bedrooms, study and gym – all with sea-view balconies.&nbsp; The spa room is set to the rear of this floor, along with a second media room.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3710" contenttypeid="BDR" desc="Bed Rooms">
      <Description><![CDATA[]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Master suite 1]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>With its lavish ensuite bathroom and superb seascapes, this bedroom is a romantic haven for couples.&nbsp; Relax and take in the views or watch TV from the king-sized bed and comfy loveseat, or indulge in a secluded soak in the freeform tub.&nbsp; Sliding glass doors open to the pool terrace and a dressing room fit for royalty enhances the suite’s ample comforts.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Master suite 2 ]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>More romance and extravagance await in the second master suite, reached through a grand marble entrance hall complete with a chandelier and exquisite art pieces.&nbsp; This king-bedded suite has a private balcony with wide sea views, a TV and an ensuite bathroom that’s a haven of cool marble luxury, with a glittering chandelier dangling above the freeform bathtub and a swish rain shower for two.&nbsp; </p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Guest bedrooms]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Although these bedrooms are smaller than the master suites, the three bedrooms offer a marble ensuite bathroom and a balcony with majestic sea views that will appeal to guests of all ages.&nbsp; The fourth bedroom has an enough work space and can use the master suite's bathroom amenities.&nbsp; All three bedrooms feature mirrored wardrobes, TVs and are furnished with a king-size bed while the fourth bedroom is a twin-bedded room convertible to double.<br /></p>    ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3711" contenttypeid="LVA" desc="Living Area">
      <Description><![CDATA[]]></Description>
      <SubContents>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Indoor living]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>Unwind or entertain with flair in Villa Haleana’s elegant open-plan living and dining area, set under a dramatically peaked timber roof and with sliding glass doors opening to the pool terrace.&nbsp; The bright guest kitchen and breakfast bar is a good spot to enjoy some snacks and refreshments, while the chef’s kitchen, where your gourmet meals are prepared, is hidden away to the side. </p><p>Media rooms equipped with TVs and DVD players are situated on both floors of the villa.&nbsp; A study with a work desk and board games offers another comfy area to relax and enjoy the sea views.&nbsp; Escape to Villa Haleana’s lower floor for a restorative workout in the gym or a relaxing massage treatment in the spa room.</p> ]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
        <SubContent>
          <Heading><![CDATA[Outdoor living]]></Heading>
          <Description><![CDATA[<p>With its 18-metre marble pool and beautiful views across Nai Thon Beach and the Andaman Sea, Villa Haleana’s sun terrace is an Instagram-ready spot.&nbsp; A dining sala for eight lies to one end of the pool while stylish black sun loungers are arranged at the opposite end.&nbsp; A table for four is set in front of a Zen garden area between the two pavilions.</p><p>A walled tropical garden offers a shady place to relax or play, while next to the villa is a cliff-top space perfect for a wedding ceremony or outdoor reception with an ocean view.</p>]]></Description>
          <Images />
        </SubContent>
      </SubContents>
    </Content>
