    <Content contentid="3713" contenttypeid="DNNG" desc="Dining">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Thai food is justifiably world famous for its fragrant and exotic flavours, and Villa Haleana’s skilled personal chef offers guests an excellent opportunity to explore this delicious cuisine and enjoy meals carefully customised to individual tastes. </p><p>The villa’s suggestion menu brims with a tasty array of Thai dishes, set breakfasts and a selection of Western dishes.&nbsp; Highlights include <span style="font-style: italic;">tom kha gai</span> (delicious chicken soup made with coconut milk and fragrant galangal); <span style="font-style: italic;">gaeng phed ped yang</span> (red curry with roasted duck); <span style="font-style: italic;">pla thod ta rod</span> (crispy sea bass with five-flavour sauce), and the chef’s specialty <span style="font-style: italic;">Gaeng ka ree nue fak tong </span>(beef tenderloin and pumpkin in Thai yellow curry). </p><p>The chef and kitchen team will take care of all the grocery shopping, sourcing only the freshest and best quality ingredients.&nbsp; Provisions are charged at cost plus a 20% handling fee and a government tax, and guests are requested to provide cash to cover groceries in advance.&nbsp; The staff will keep receipts for reference when settling the bills. </p><p>Villa Haleana’s setting is as delectable as its cuisine.&nbsp; Whether you opt to dine in the elegant indoor dining area or alfresco on the pool terrace, you’ll be perfectly placed to enjoy the spectacular sea and sunset panoramas.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3714" contenttypeid="FAM" desc="Families">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>With its bright, airy living spaces, modern facilities, walled garden and friendly staff team, Villa Haleana extends a warm welcome to families. </p><p>A lift provides easy access for pushchair-bound youngsters and less-mobile elders, while exclusive use of the 18-metre pool gives families the freedom to splash and play without worrying about other guests.&nbsp; (There’s no safety fence, so a careful eye will need to be kept on non-swimmers.)&nbsp; The media room next to the upper-floor master suite can be converted to a child’s room if needed. </p><p>Children’s equipment, including high chairs, baby cots, changing tables and car seats can be sourced from local rental agencies for a small extra fee – just let us know your requirements when making your villa reservation.&nbsp; Likewise, if you fancy a night out during your stay, a reliable babysitting service can be arranged (extra charges apply).</p><p>Keeping the whole family happy and well fed is easy at Villa Haleana.&nbsp; Young guests will have fun choosing their own dishes from the villa menu, and the chef is open to discuss any special requests for meals and snacks, whether it’s toning down the spice level in a curry or having sandwiches sliced just so.&nbsp; Delicious Thai treats, such as chicken satay skewers, mango sticky rice or <span style="font-style: italic;">pad Thai</span> noodles, might just be the keys to unlock picky eaters’ taste buds. &nbsp;</p><p>Though Villa Haleana holds plenty of charm for families, having one of Phuket’s most beautiful beaches on your doorstep is an added bonus.&nbsp; Grab those buckets and spades and go sand-castle building on Nai Thon’s powdery sands, which remain blissfully free of crowds year round.&nbsp; Treat the kids to some fast food, Thai style – fresh corn on the cob and skewers of grilled meat are readily available from local vendors.&nbsp; Snorkelling, stand-up paddling and boat trips are just a few of the activities on offer, but check our <a href="./the-locale/things-to-do.html" target="_blank" title="Malaiwana - things to do">Things to Do</a> page for more ideas and be sure to chat with the villa staff for their recommendations and assistance with booking transport and tours.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3718" contenttypeid="GYM" desc="Gym">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>Villa Haleana’s air-conditioned gym is available to guests 24 hours a day.&nbsp; This fitness room has floor-to-ceiling windows to enjoy sea views while working out, and is well equipped with a treadmill, elliptical trainer, yoga mats, fit balls and a weight-training station.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3719" contenttypeid="SPA" desc="Spa">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>A relaxing spa treatment is a must at Haleana. The villa’s marble spa room is designed like a heavenly Turkish bath with spa beds, a steam sauna and a spa shower. Its jacuzzi, grandly elevated on a marble platform, is big enough for four people to relax in comfortably. There’s even a beauty salon with a reclining chair and sink for hair styling – perfect for brides and their entourage to prepare for the big event. Curtains between the massage area, the salon and the jacuzzi area offer added privacy for groups.</p><p>Phuket is home to many professional spa and beauty specialists, and your villa manager can arrange for the best to provide private in-villa treatments. Thai massage, oil massage, facials, manicures and pedicures are just some of the choices available. Refer to the spa menu at the villa for more details.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
    <Content contentid="3739" contenttypeid="EHVD" desc="EH Villa Description">
      <Description><![CDATA[<p>With its modern glamour, tropical setting and inspiring ocean views, six-bedroomed Villa Haleana is the perfect destination for families or groups of friends celebrating a special occasion or holidaying in style.&nbsp; As part of the exclusive Malaiwana estate, overlooking the pristine Nai Thon Beach, Villa Haleana is ideally located for exploring the picturesque northwest Phuket coastline, a lesser-travelled area with miles of soft-sand beaches, lush rural landscapes and jungle-clad hills. </p><p>Elegant and graceful, the villa’s peak-roofed pavilions are inspired by traditional Thai architecture and its modern interiors are swathed in cool marble, with polished wood accents.&nbsp; Generous indoor and outdoor living areas are set over two floors connected by a lift and staircase. </p><p>A superb retreat for a rejuvenating holiday, the villa has a private 18-metre pool and its own ultra-luxe spa room and gym, plus multiple areas to rest, dine and entertain in style.&nbsp; Both master suites feature huge bathrooms fit for royalty, and all bedrooms offer glorious views.&nbsp; With a team of full-time staff that includes a talented Thai chef and knowledgeable villa manager, your every need will be catered to, within the villa and beyond. </p><p>As a wedding and event venue, the villa is sure to impress – not only for its breath-taking views but with its excellent entertainment facilities and picture-perfect terrace and gardens.&nbsp; For larger groups, Malaiwana estate offers an exceptional choice of accommodation.&nbsp; In addition to Villa Haleana, rental options include 4-bedroomed <a href="http://www.elitehavens.com/malaiwana-residence-duplex-c2-villa/-phuket-thailand.aspx" target="_self" title="Malaiwana - Duplex, 4 bedrooms">Duplex</a> and <a href="http://www.elitehavens.com/malaiwana-residence-penthouse-c1-villa/-phuket-thailand.aspx" target="_self" title="Malaiwana - Penthouse, 4+1 bedrooms">Penthouse</a> Residences, 5-bedroomed <a href="http://www.elitehavens.com/malaiwana-villa-m-villa/nai-thon-phuket-thailand.aspx" target="_self" title="Malaiwana Villa M, 5 bedroom villa">Villa M</a> and 4-bedroomed <a href="http://www.elitehavens.com/malaiwana-villa-rodnaya-villa/nai-thon-phuket-thailand.aspx" target="_self" title="Malaiwana Villa Rodnaya, 4 bedroom villa">Villa Rodnaya</a>.<br /></p><p>Beautiful Nai Thon Beach, a serene one-kilometre stretch of powder-soft sand, is just down the hill. Relax on the sands, snorkel, standup paddle or sample some fresh grilled seafood from one of the seaside vendors.&nbsp; Phuket Airport is just nine kilometres away and many island highlights including golf, beach clubs and yacht charters are within easy reach of Villa Haleana.</p>]]></Description>
      <SubContents />
    </Content>
